%N A387977 Triangle T(n,k) read by rows, where T(n,k) = number of heapable permutations of length n with exactly k inversions.
%C A387977 A permutation of [1..n] is heapable if it can be inserted, one element at a time, into a binary min-heap without violating the heap property.
%C A387977 An inversion in a permutation p of length n is a pair of indices (i,j) with i<j such that p(i)>p(j).
%C A387977 The total number of inversions is the number of such pairs.
